Subject: PostgreSQL 17.2 Released!

The PostgreSQL Global Development Group announces the release of PostgreSQL 17.2,
the latest version of the world's most advanced open source database.

This release includes important security fixes and bug fixes. All users are
encouraged to upgrade as soon as possible.

Key improvements in this release:
- Improved query planner performance
- Enhanced JSON support
- Better partitioning capabilities

For the full list of changes, see the release notes at:
https://www.postgresql.org/docs/17/release-17-2.html

Download: https://www.postgresql.org/download/

