Subject: PostgreSQL 18 Development Update

The PostgreSQL development team is excited to share an update on
PostgreSQL 18, currently in development.

New features being worked on include:
- Native support for vector operations (pgvector integration)
- Improved logical replication performance
- Enhanced parallel query capabilities
- Better memory management for large workloads

Alpha 1 is expected in March 2026.

Stay tuned for more updates!

